definition.value: A 6-phospho-beta-D-glucosyl-(1->4)-D-glucose in which the anomeric centre at the reducing end has beta-configuration.
Any amine formally derived from ammonia by replacing one, two or three hydrogen atoms by alkyl groups.
A sesquiterpene lactone obtained from sweet wormwood, Artemisia annua, which is used as an antimalarial for the treatment of multi-drug resistant strains of falciparum malaria.
